<div id="p492" class="blockpost rowodd firstpost">
	<h2><span><span class="conr">#1&nbsp;</span><a href="viewtopic.php?pid=492#p492">2008-09-11 22:12:49</a></span></h2>
	<div class="box">
		<div class="inbox">
			<div class="postleft">
				<dl>
					<dt><strong><a href="profile.php?id=90022">sren</a></strong></dt>
					<dd class="usertitle"><strong>Member</strong></dd>
					<dd class="postavatar"></dd>
				</dl>
			</div>
			<div class="postright">
				<h3>Top-BT: a BT client to speed downloading twice with less traffic</h3>
				<div class="postmsg">
					<p>Hi,<br /><br />We are researchers at the Ohio State University. We have implemented and released a new BitTorrent client software written in Python, called Top-BT. Different from previously released BT client, Top-BT actively discovers Internet topology, and uses this intelligence to always choose close peers to download file pieces. We have extensively evaluated and tested our client. Our study shows that, compared to native BT clients, Top-BT can accelerate downloading up to twice, but save up to 40% induced Internet traffic.<br /><br />You all are very welcome to try out our Top-BT client, and give us some advice, suggestions, and comments. Currently the Top-BT client can be downloaded from two places:<br /><br /><a href="http://sourceforge.net/projects/top-bt/" rel="nofollow">http://sourceforge.net/projects/top-bt/</a><br /><a href="http://www.cse.ohio-state.edu/~sren/topbt/" rel="nofollow">http://www.cse.ohio-state.edu/~sren/topbt/</a><br /><br />Regards,<br />Shansi</p>
				</div>
			</div>
			<div class="clearer"></div>
			<div class="postfootleft"><p>Offline</p></div>
			<div class="postfootright"><div>&nbsp;</div></div>
		</div>
	</div>
</div>

